<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>A.D 2000X in Tokyo, a mysterious occurrence of overflowing Blocks was halted by the actions of a Professional Excavator "Driller" by the name of SusumuHori. Above ground, peace returned again.
                  <br><br>Half a year passed, suddenly the Blocks began to overflow in three nations.One after another America, India and Egypt became flooded in blocks.
                  <br><br>Susumu Hori and his Rival Driller, Anna Hottenmeyer; urgently began to dig to the depths of the earth. Meanwhile, Susumu's father, Taizou Hori; Susumu'selder brother, Ataru Hori; Anna's Robot Assistant, Horinger Z and Susumu's roomate, Puchi, were all digging to the depths of the earth, aiming for the resolution of this disaster.
                  <br><br>What is the probable cause of this latest incident?
                  <br>And, among the 6 Drillers, who will be the one to resolve this disaster?
                  <br><br>Our hero can drill up, down, left and right. Drilling through single blocks would take forever, so it's fortunate that blocks of the same color form into groups that vanish when only one of the blocks is drilled. This allows for chain reactions, since vanishing blocks will often cause other blocks to fall and form new groups. Alas, these falling blocks are also deadly if they hit Mr. Driller.
                  <br><br>If all Mr. Driller had to do was drill, life would be easy. But he also has to keep refilling his oxygen supply by collecting air capsules scattered throughout the blocks. The deeper he goes, the faster his air runs out. Hampering his progress even further are brown "X-blocks" that take five drill strikes to disappear and remove 20% of Mr. Driller's air when broken.
                  <br><br>CHARACTERS:
                  <br>- Susumu Hori:
                  <br>The hero of this game. Presently the boy closest to the highest Driller grade"Mr. Driller". Recommended for all players.
                  <br>Movement Speed: Average
                  <br>Air Consumption: Average
                  <br>Special Ability: Nothing
                  <br><br>Anna Hottenmayer:
                  <br>A girl of German birth. She is Susumu's Rival and a fiery Elite Driller. She is as equally capable as Susumu, maybe even more so. Recommended for intermediate players.
                  <br>Movement Speed: Fairly Fast
                  <br>Air Consumption: Fairly Fast
                  <br>Special Ability: Nothing
                  <br><br>Taizou Hori:
                  <br>The father of Susumu. He resolved the Dig Dug incident of 1982 and in thefollowing year, the Nankoku Island War (Dig Dug II) all on his own. This madehim become a global hero.Recommended for advance players.
                  <br>Movement Speed: Fairly Slow
                  <br>Air Consumption: Fast
                  <br>Special Ability: Destroys Blocks instantaneously.
                  <br><br>Ataru Hori:
                  <br>Older brother of Susumu. He had a falling out with his father, Taizou Hori and ran away from home some years ago. Since then his whereabouts have been unknown. His abilities as a Driller are first class. Recommended for advance players.
                  <br>Movement Speed: Very Fast
                  <br>Air Consumption: Fast
                  <br>Special Ability: Nothing
                  <br><br>- Puchi:
                  <br>A stray dog, Susumu collected it from the street and took it in to live with him in his house. It is a dog genius who can talk and do housekeeping. Recommended for beginners.
                  <br>Movement Speed: Fairly Slow
                  <br>Air Consumption: Fairly Slow
                  <br>Special Ability: Can climb 2 Blocks high.
                  <br><br>- Horinger Z:
                  <br>The prototype robot developed by Dr. Zett, used for extreme work. It can transform into a drill and tunnel underground. Recommended for beginners.
                  <br>Movement Speed: Fairly Slow
                  <br>Air Consumption: Fairly Slow
                  <br>Special Ability: Can withstand 1 Block falling on it.
                  <br><br>- Usagi:
                  <br>A mysterious space creature which has taken the form of a rabbit. Only playable after clearing the secret North Pole Stage in Mission Driller. Recommended for very advance players.
                  <br>Movement Speed: Very Fast
                  <br>Air Consumption: Fast
                  <br>Special Ability: Can climb 2 Blocks high, destroys Blocks instantaneously and has permanent Three Way.
                  <br><br>GAME MODES:
                  <br>Mission driller:
                  <br>The basic Mr. Driller Game, dig down deep in many locations around the world.
                  <br><br>Scenario Driller:
                  <br>Roleplay as Susumu and other Drillers as you follow an animated story and take part in various activities (mainly DriStone Stages).
                  <br><br>- Time Attack Driller
                  <br>With Time Attack mode you are required to dig to given depth within the allocated time.
                  <br><br>2 PLAYER GAME MODES:
                  <br>- Driller Race
                  <br>2 Players race head-to-head in a randomly generated level to reach a depth of 500 metres
first. The courses are very much like a Mission Driller courses, except Crystal Blocks and White
Blocks are absent.
                  <br><br>- Driller Survival:
                  <br>2 Players compete to outlast the other in a randomly generated level, filled with items common with Time Attack Driller, which alter the opposition's playfield. Making it harder for them to survive. The lives each player begins with is set individually before play (between 1-5).
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Mr. Driller digging action comes back to evolution! Dig your goals, "Misshondorira", aims to dig the fastest time "Taimuatakkudorira" game mode "Dorirasabaibaru", in addition to the goal of competing in two speed "Doriraresu" new features. Became more intense battle enjoy digging.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>SCI-FI & Fantasy themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

